	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Pretoria - A Zimbabwean man suffered severe spinal injuries and a loss of sensation to his legs after he was hit on the back with a panga in Hammanskraal on Saturday morning, paramedics said. The 22-year-old was allegedly attacked and robbed by unknown people, Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha said. He was airlifted to hospital in a Netcare medical helicopter. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  